<h2 id="summary">2. SUMMARY OF KEY POINTS</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>What personal information do we process?</strong> Account information you provide (such as name, email, and username), conversation content you submit through the App, and information automatically collected through your use of the Services (such as device and usage data).</li>
  <li><strong>Do we process sensitive personal information?</strong> Yes. We explicitly collect political opinions as part of the App's core functionality. We do not ask you to provide other sensitive personal information (such as data revealing racial or ethnic origin, religious beliefs, health, or sexual orientation), but this type of information may incidentally appear if you choose to include it in a conversation. See Section 3.</li>
  <li><strong>Do we use your information to improve and train our AI models?</strong> Yes. Conversation data you submit may be used to evaluate, improve, and train or fine-tune the AI models underlying the App. See Section 5.</li>
  <li><strong>Do we share your information with third parties?</strong> We use third-party AI service providers, including Anthropic, to process and respond to your inputs. We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties for their own marketing purposes.</li>
  <li><strong>How do you exercise your rights?</strong> Contact us at <a href="mailto:spencer@spencerfrank.com">spencer@spencerfrank.com</a>, or submit a data subject access request as described in Section 12.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="collect">3. WHAT INFORMATION DO WE COLLECT?</h2>
<h3>Personal information you disclose to us</h3>
<p>
  We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide when you register for or use the Services, participate in beta testing activities, or otherwise contact us. This may include:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>names</li>
  <li>email addresses</li>
  <li>usernames and account credentials</li>
  <li>political opinions or affiliations you provide as part of using the App's core features</li>
  <li>conversation content and other input you submit through the App</li>
</ul>
<p>
  All personal information you provide must be true, accurate, and current, and you must notify us of any changes.
</p>
<h3>Sensitive information</h3>
<p>
  We explicitly collect political opinions as part of the App's core functionality, and by using the Services and providing this information, you consent to our processing of it as described in this Policy, including for the AI training and improvement purposes described in Section 5.
</p>
<p>
  We do not ask you to provide other categories of sensitive personal information (such as data revealing racial or ethnic origin, religious or philosophical beliefs, health information, or sexual orientation). However, because the App accepts open-ended conversational input, this type of information may incidentally appear if you choose to include it in a message. If you do, we process and retain it in the same manner as other conversation content described in this Policy, including for the AI training purposes described in Section 5, unless you choose not to include it. We also process account login credentials as sensitive personal information, only as necessary to operate the Services.
</p>
<p>
  You have the right to limit our use of sensitive personal information — including political opinions — to purposes necessary to provide the Services, and we will honor requests to do so; contact us at <a href="mailto:spencer@spencerfrank.com">spencer@spencerfrank.com</a> to make such a request. See Section 12 for more on your rights regarding sensitive personal information.
</p>
<p>
  The Services are offered solely to residents of the United States during the beta period; see Section 1. Because the Services are not offered outside the United States, this Policy is written with reference to United States privacy law and does not address obligations under non-US frameworks such as the EU General Data Protection Regulation.
</p>
<h3>Information automatically collected</h3>
<p>
  We automatically collect certain information when you use the Services, including device information, IP address, browser and operating system details, log and usage data (such as crash reports, error logs, feature usage, and session timestamps), and diagnostic and telemetry data specific to the beta program. This information is used primarily to operate, secure, and improve the Services during the beta period.
</p>

<h2 id="process">4. HOW DO WE PROCESS YOUR INFORMATION?</h2>
<p>We process your personal information for the following purposes:</p>
<ul>
  <li>To create and manage your account, including authentication.</li>
  <li>To provide, operate, and deliver the Services you request.</li>
  <li>To respond to inquiries and provide support.</li>
  <li>To request and process feedback about the beta program.</li>
  <li>To identify usage trends and evaluate and improve the Services, including troubleshooting and diagnosing issues during the beta period.</li>
  <li>To train, fine-tune, evaluate, and otherwise improve the AI models that power the App, including future versions, using conversation data and other content you submit. See Section 5 for more detail.</li>
  <li>To maintain the security and integrity of the Services and prevent fraud or abuse.</li>
  <li>To comply with legal obligations.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="ai">5. DO WE OFFER ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE-BASED PRODUCTS?</h2>
<p>
  As part of the Services, we offer features powered by artificial intelligence and machine learning ("AI Products"). This section describes two distinct uses of your data in connection with AI Products, which we want to be clear about separately.
</p>
<h3>Serving your requests</h3>
<p>
  We use third-party AI service providers, including Anthropic, to process your inputs and generate responses within the App. Your input, output, and related personal information are shared with these providers under contractual terms restricting their use of your data to providing this service to us, consistent with Section 6 below.
</p>
<h3>Training and improving our own models</h3>
<p>
  Separately from the above, because the App is currently in beta, we may use conversation data and other content you submit through the Services to train, fine-tune, evaluate, and otherwise improve the AI models underlying the App, including future versions. By using the Services during the beta period, you consent to this use of your conversation data. Where technically feasible, we may take steps to identify and exclude sensitive personal information from training data; however, because conversation content is open-ended, we cannot guarantee complete removal of any sensitive personal information you choose to include in your messages. You may request that we limit the use of sensitive personal information you have submitted, as described in Section 3.
</p>

<h2 id="share">6. WHEN AND WITH WHOM DO WE SHARE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION?</h2>
<p>We may share information in the following situations:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Service Providers.</strong> We disclose personal information to service providers who perform services on our behalf, including AI service providers (such as Anthropic), hosting providers, and analytics providers, pursuant to written contracts that restrict their use of your information to providing services to us.</li>
  <li><strong>Business Transfers.</strong> We may share or transfer your information in connection with, or during negotiations of, any merger, sale of company assets, financing, or acquisition of all or a portion of our business.</li>
  <li><strong>Legal Obligations.</strong> We may disclose information where required to comply with a legal obligation, protect our rights, or investigate potential violations of our Terms of Use.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Disclosures to service providers under the restrictions described above are not considered a "sale" or "share" of personal information under applicable law. Apart from these situations, we have not sold or shared personal information with third parties for their own marketing or commercial purposes in the preceding twelve (12) months, and we do not intend to do so.
</p>

<h2 id="retain">7. HOW LONG DO WE KEEP YOUR INFORMATION?</h2>
<p>
  We keep your personal information only as long as necessary for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer period is required by law. Account information is generally retained for as long as you maintain an account with us. Conversation data used for the AI training purposes described in Section 5 may be retained separately from your account for as long as reasonably necessary to support model development, in de-identified or aggregated form where feasible.
</p>

<h2 id="safe">8. HOW DO WE KEEP YOUR INFORMATION SAFE?</h2>
<p>
  We use reasonable technical and organizational security measures designed to protect your personal information. However, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee that unauthorized third parties will never be able to defeat our security measures. Use of the Services is at your own risk.
</p>

<h2 id="minors">9. DO WE COLLECT INFORMATION FROM MINORS?</h2>
<p>
  We do not knowingly collect data from or market to children under 18 years of age. By using the Services, you represent that you are at least 18. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a user under 18, we will deactivate the account and delete such data as reasonably possible. Contact us at <a href="mailto:spencer@spencerfrank.com">spencer@spencerfrank.com</a> if you become aware of any such data.
</p>

<h2 id="rights">10. WHAT ARE YOUR PRIVACY RIGHTS?</h2>
<p>
  You may review, update, or delete your account information at any time by contacting us at <a href="mailto:spencer@spencerfrank.com">spencer@spencerfrank.com</a>. If we are relying on your consent to process your information, you may withdraw that consent at any time; this will not affect the lawfulness of processing before withdrawal. Upon request to terminate your account, we will deactivate or delete your information from our active systems, except where retention is necessary for legal, security, or fraud-prevention purposes.
</p>

<h2 id="dnt">11. CONTROLS FOR DO-NOT-TRACK FEATURES</h2>
<p>
  Most browsers and some mobile operating systems include a Do-Not-Track ("DNT") feature. Because no uniform standard for recognizing DNT signals currently exists, we do not respond to DNT signals at this time. If a standard is adopted that we must follow, we will update this Privacy Policy accordingly.
</p>

